WEBVTT

00:01.035 --> 00:03.348
You just name one really good death.

00:03.669 --> 00:04.802
[snaps fingers, gunshot]

00:04.837 --> 00:06.437
Previously on <i>Smash...</i>

00:06.471 --> 00:07.605
I'm not the star anymore, am I?

00:07.640 --> 00:09.741
Guess you should've slept with
Derek when you had the chance.

00:09.742 --> 00:11.142
I got you something.

00:11.176 --> 00:13.444
It's the only project for us.
I knew you'd agree.

00:13.479 --> 00:16.180
[Cheers and applause]

00:16.215 --> 00:17.548
I cannot wait to see
what he's gonna do

00:17.583 --> 00:19.484
with <i>City of Angels.</i>

00:19.518 --> 00:21.853
Right now, what I care about
is directing.

00:21.887 --> 00:23.254
Both:
♪ I've been a puppet

00:23.289 --> 00:25.456
♪ a pauper, a pirate, a poet ♪

00:25.491 --> 00:26.891
Let's go to Broadway.

00:26.926 --> 00:28.192
<i>Gatsby</i> would've made me happy.

00:28.227 --> 00:30.295
Then do <i>Gatsby.</i>

00:30.329 --> 00:33.665
Nothing Jimmy has ever said
has checked out.

00:33.699 --> 00:35.366
I wasn't a good person,
but ever since I met you,

00:35.401 --> 00:36.534
that's all I want to be.

00:36.569 --> 00:38.469
Hey, hey, it's time for you
to leave.

00:38.504 --> 00:40.271
[Crowd gasps]
You scare me, Jimmy.

00:40.306 --> 00:41.472
You asked to get to know me,

00:41.507 --> 00:43.408
and now you're walking away,
of course!

00:43.780 --> 00:46.753
Sync and corrected by dr.jackson
for www.addic7ed.com

00:46.946 --> 00:49.414
Once a year,
Broadway opens its generous arms

00:49.448 --> 00:52.083
to musical theater students
all over the country.

00:52.117 --> 00:54.117
They fly here to New York,
they see shows at night,

00:54.119 --> 00:56.654
and during the day,
they take master classes

00:56.689 --> 00:58.690
with actual Broadway performers.

00:58.724 --> 01:02.293
Today we've asked Ivy Lynn
and the cast of <i>Bombshell</i>

01:02.328 --> 01:04.028
to teach these eager students
how to do

01:04.063 --> 01:06.397
"the 20th Century Fox mambo."
Rah!

01:06.432 --> 01:08.466
And that's why
I'm all dressed like this.

01:08.500 --> 01:10.468
Hey, Ivy, girl.

01:10.502 --> 01:12.370
What a whirlwind
you have been on.

01:12.404 --> 01:13.805
You did four shows
over the weekend,

01:13.839 --> 01:15.273
and you flew
out to Los Angeles,

01:15.307 --> 01:17.108
did <i>Leno</i> last night,
got on the red-eye,

01:17.142 --> 01:20.144
and here you are with us
today on the <i>Today Show.</i>

01:20.179 --> 01:21.579
It must be exhausting.

01:21.614 --> 01:23.581
No, it's exhilarating,
kathie Lee.

01:23.616 --> 01:24.782
Great.

01:24.817 --> 01:26.084
Are you ready to mambo with me?

01:26.118 --> 01:27.619
- I'm ready, girl. Let's do it.
- All right.

01:27.653 --> 01:30.622
Okay, kids,
watch how it's done.

01:35.661 --> 01:38.630
<i>[The 20th Century Fox mambo]</i>

01:38.664 --> 01:40.264
♪

01:45.705 --> 01:48.139
♪ In this factory
where dreams can come true ♪

01:48.173 --> 01:50.308
♪ are you ready
to make someone new? ♪

01:50.342 --> 01:53.111
♪ you're the team
that must teach me to do ♪

01:53.145 --> 01:56.347
♪ the 20th Century Fox mambo ♪

01:56.382 --> 01:59.083
♪ done the homework
and I'll pass the test ♪

01:59.118 --> 02:01.920
♪ I'll do whatever
my teachers suggest ♪

02:01.954 --> 02:04.522
♪ I can do it clothed
or undressed ♪

02:04.557 --> 02:08.092
♪ the 20th Century Fox mambo ♪

02:08.127 --> 02:10.461
♪ make it up, shake it up

02:10.496 --> 02:12.697
ensemble:
♪ let the fantasies begin

02:12.731 --> 02:13.798
here's the dope.

02:13.832 --> 02:15.800
♪ To get cast,
change the past ♪

02:15.834 --> 02:17.468
♪ make the light
just right for sin... ♪

02:17.503 --> 02:18.836
♪ emascope

02:18.871 --> 02:21.172
- ♪ take a gamble
- Where's Julia?

02:21.206 --> 02:24.375
It's not like her to miss
out on something like this.

02:24.410 --> 02:26.010
I left her a message.

02:26.045 --> 02:27.178
♪ The 20th Century Fox

02:27.213 --> 02:28.846
I thought you two
were living together.

02:28.881 --> 02:30.415
She moved out last week.

02:30.449 --> 02:32.750
Hmm.

02:32.785 --> 02:34.519
What?
That was always the plan.

02:34.553 --> 02:36.354
She found a really cute place.

02:36.388 --> 02:37.655
We're totally fine.

02:37.690 --> 02:40.692
I think you and Julia
should probably be planning

02:40.726 --> 02:42.226
your next project together,

02:42.261 --> 02:45.830
after she's finished writing
on <i>Gatsby.</i>

02:45.864 --> 02:47.966
What? <i>Gatsby?</i>

02:48.000 --> 02:49.534
I'm sorry.
You didn't know?

02:49.568 --> 02:52.303
Scott Nichols announced it
to his board

02:52.338 --> 02:53.738
just earlier this week.

02:53.772 --> 02:55.473
♪ When we're finished ♪
♪ he'll never forget ♪

02:55.507 --> 02:57.842
ensemble:
♪ the 20th Century Fox

02:57.876 --> 03:01.179
A little to your left, Ana.

03:01.213 --> 03:02.480
Yep.

03:02.514 --> 03:04.148
Just loosen up.
Just let go.

03:04.183 --> 03:06.751
You don't... you don't really
want to kill her.

03:06.785 --> 03:10.488
You know?
It's all in fun.

03:10.522 --> 03:13.791
- So you're still seeing him?
- Yes, I am.

03:13.826 --> 03:15.927
Adam's funny.
He makes me laugh.

03:15.961 --> 03:18.129
Okay, we are all set
with these two.

03:18.163 --> 03:19.297
Now I need the guy.

03:19.331 --> 03:20.732
He was supposed to be here
two hours ago.

03:20.766 --> 03:22.567
Yeah, uh...

03:22.601 --> 03:24.235
I'm sure he'll be here
any minute, Patrick.

03:24.270 --> 03:26.070
You know he left
in his costume last night.

03:26.105 --> 03:27.605
[Sighs]

03:27.640 --> 03:30.008
You know, Rudin's called me
twice already this morning.

03:30.042 --> 03:31.109
He's practically
writing a check

03:31.143 --> 03:32.303
to move <i>Hit lis</i> t to Broadway,

03:32.311 --> 03:33.945
and he hasn't even seen it yet.

03:33.979 --> 03:35.647
Well, let him Duke it out
with the ten other producers

03:35.681 --> 03:37.081
that are coming.

03:37.116 --> 03:39.050
That was a great idea, having
them come on the same night.

03:39.084 --> 03:40.218
Mm hmm.

03:40.252 --> 03:43.121
Yep, Daryl Roth, David Stone,
Kevin McCollum.

03:43.155 --> 03:45.523
Tell you what,
if a bomb goes off tonight,

03:45.557 --> 03:47.392
Broadway as we know it
will probably cease to exist.

03:47.426 --> 03:48.826
[Chuckles]

03:48.861 --> 03:51.696
Derek, we need your help.

03:51.730 --> 03:53.998
Where's Jimmy?

03:54.033 --> 03:55.800
I left him a bunch of messages.

03:55.834 --> 03:57.468
I'm sure he just has
the wrong time.

03:57.503 --> 03:59.003
They told me
they'd pull the cover

03:59.038 --> 04:00.972
if we didn't have him here.

04:01.006 --> 04:02.640
It's obviously some
adolescent cry for help,

04:02.675 --> 04:04.776
which I do not have time for.

04:04.810 --> 04:06.010
He's just under
a lot of pressure.

04:06.045 --> 04:08.313
Oh, is he? Poor baby.
Well, so am I.

04:08.347 --> 04:10.148
If he keeps this up,
he's not gonna see out the run.

04:10.182 --> 04:12.116
Just get him here now.

04:14.353 --> 04:18.156
Do you know where he is?

04:18.190 --> 04:23.094
He didn't come home last night.

04:23.128 --> 04:24.128
Did you have fun?

04:24.129 --> 04:25.530
Kids: Yeah!

04:25.564 --> 04:27.398
High fives!
Good job.

04:27.433 --> 04:28.566
Chop chop, Ivy.

04:28.601 --> 04:29.801
You don't want to be late
for your signing

04:29.835 --> 04:31.169
at the Macy's sweater sale.

04:31.203 --> 04:32.370
[Cell phone rings]
You've got Agnes.

04:32.404 --> 04:33.705
So you've got the matinee

04:33.739 --> 04:35.306
and then you have
the interview.

04:35.341 --> 04:38.409
Tonight's show,
and then my own bed, my DVR,

04:38.444 --> 04:40.578
and the entire season
of <i>girl</i> that I missed.

04:40.613 --> 04:43.848
Wait, wait, wait, you forgot
about <i>Broadway talks back.</i>

04:43.882 --> 04:46.684
Oh, my God,
the Tom and Julia Q&Q.

04:46.719 --> 04:49.520
Moderated by their star,
Ivy Lynn.

04:49.555 --> 04:52.557
Don't worry, you'll make
half-hour before performance.

04:56.028 --> 04:59.063
Marisa Tomei broke her leg.

04:59.098 --> 05:00.765
Which means...

05:00.799 --> 05:04.002
<i>Moonstruck</i> won't be going
to Broadway this season.

05:04.036 --> 05:06.037
<i>Imitation of life</i>
is D.O.A.

05:06.071 --> 05:08.339
The Lloyd Webber just posted
their closing notice.

05:08.374 --> 05:11.442
So if we stay open till June,

05:11.477 --> 05:12.977
that Tony is ours.

05:13.012 --> 05:14.646
That may be harder
than we thought.

05:14.680 --> 05:15.947
Advance sales aren't
what they should be.

05:15.981 --> 05:17.482
We haven't gone a day
without being

05:17.516 --> 05:19.417
on the T.K.T.S. board
since we opened.

05:19.451 --> 05:21.986
Well, what about we launch
a new radio campaign?

05:22.021 --> 05:25.490
Not unless you have
a sugar daddy I'm not aware of.

05:25.524 --> 05:27.625
Well, you'd better pray
for a miracle, then,

05:27.660 --> 05:31.162
'cause we're gonna need one
to stay open till June.

05:31.196 --> 05:32.797
So I started writing.

05:32.831 --> 05:34.933
And it just flowed.

05:34.967 --> 05:37.168
And I just lost track of time.

05:37.202 --> 05:39.304
Please stop making excuses
and just tell me

05:39.338 --> 05:41.005
what you're doing with <i>Gatsby.</i>

05:41.040 --> 05:43.308
Obviously, I'm not doing it
as a musical.

05:43.342 --> 05:45.743
I'm writing a play.

05:45.778 --> 05:47.111
<i>Gatsby</i> is our dream project.

05:47.146 --> 05:49.347
We've been talking about it
for a decade.

05:49.381 --> 05:51.049
Which is why I bought it
and wrapped it up

05:51.083 --> 05:52.317
in a bow for you.

05:52.351 --> 05:54.185
You said you didn't want it.

05:54.220 --> 05:55.520
I wanted it.

05:55.554 --> 05:57.088
I just didn't want it
right at that second.

05:57.122 --> 05:59.257
I thought I'd be tied up
directing for six months.

05:59.291 --> 06:01.559
But then that never
came through.

06:01.593 --> 06:03.027
I'm sorry about that.

06:03.062 --> 06:04.295
But I've already set things
in motion.

06:04.330 --> 06:06.631
I spoke with the estate.
I promised it to Scott.

06:06.665 --> 06:09.200
Well, now you can
un-promise it

06:09.234 --> 06:10.702
and start working on it
with me,

06:10.736 --> 06:13.171
your partner.

06:13.205 --> 06:16.207
See you tonight?

06:20.012 --> 06:21.813
- Patrick, where are you going?
- I waited three hours.

06:21.847 --> 06:23.848
Your boy's not coming.

06:23.882 --> 06:25.183
No, wait, he's...
He's coming right now.

06:25.217 --> 06:26.884
He's on his way.
It'll be an inside spread now.

06:26.919 --> 06:28.353
But that's still great, Derek.

06:28.387 --> 06:29.854
- Uh-huh.
- [Laughing]

06:29.888 --> 06:32.357
- Oh, no.
- All right, all right.

06:32.391 --> 06:34.325
[Laughing]
Can somebody help us?

06:34.360 --> 06:35.793
- Nice.
- Whoo! Whoo!

06:38.931 --> 06:39.964
[Huffs]

06:39.999 --> 06:41.065
Bye.

06:41.100 --> 06:42.900
Hey.

06:42.935 --> 06:45.503
What'd I miss, huh?

06:45.537 --> 06:47.872
No?

06:47.907 --> 06:48.907
Hit it.

