07:19.018 --> 07:20.518
Hey!

07:20.928 --> 07:24.831
Just when I thought my day
couldn't get any better.

07:24.865 --> 07:28.368
- Hi.
- Hi. Mmm.

07:28.402 --> 07:29.502
Look at this.

07:29.536 --> 07:30.770
Mm.

07:30.804 --> 07:32.105
It's a guest list for tonight.

07:32.139 --> 07:34.240
It's like the who's who
of American theater.

07:34.274 --> 07:35.308
That's so great.

07:35.342 --> 07:36.776
And I just finished reading

07:36.810 --> 07:40.179
the most amazing opening scene

07:40.214 --> 07:41.347
of this new play I'm producing.

07:41.382 --> 07:43.249
It's based on <i>The Great Gatsby,</i>

07:43.283 --> 07:46.819
and its writer is going to win
a Tony for it someday.

07:46.854 --> 07:47.887
Scott...

07:47.921 --> 07:49.689
I can't stop thinking about it.

07:49.723 --> 07:50.990
I mean, it's not just
an adaptation.

07:51.025 --> 07:52.025
It stands on its own.

07:52.026 --> 07:53.192
If you keep this up,

07:53.227 --> 07:55.294
people are gonna be doing
your version

07:55.329 --> 07:58.598
for years to come.

07:58.632 --> 08:01.601
I screwed up.

08:01.635 --> 08:05.338
Tom doesn't want
to let go of <i>Gatsby.</i>

08:05.372 --> 08:08.374
He wants to do it with me.

08:12.012 --> 08:14.814
[Groans softly]

08:17.918 --> 08:19.619
Of course he does.

08:19.653 --> 08:22.188
I'm so sorry.

08:22.222 --> 08:23.523
I know I said
that I wouldn't break

08:23.557 --> 08:24.924
another promise to you,
and now here I am

08:24.958 --> 08:26.459
doing just that.

08:26.493 --> 08:27.933
You gave Tom the choice
to do <i>Gatsby.</i>

08:27.961 --> 08:29.162
He said no.

08:29.196 --> 08:32.198
He and I have a history
with the project.

08:32.232 --> 08:33.299
It's complicated.

08:33.332 --> 08:35.068
No, it's simple.

08:35.102 --> 08:36.969
He lost his directing gig.

08:37.004 --> 08:39.505
Now he's scrambling.

08:39.539 --> 08:43.643
Julia, you said that we
would work on this together.

08:43.677 --> 08:44.744
I told my board.

08:44.778 --> 08:46.179
I know.

08:46.213 --> 08:48.214
Let me tell you something
you don't know.

08:48.248 --> 08:51.351
In order to make <i>Hit List</i>
everything it needs to be,

08:51.385 --> 08:54.921
I spent some of the reserves
of next season's budget on it.

08:54.955 --> 08:56.456
If it doesn't transfer
to Broadway,

08:56.490 --> 08:58.691
I have to follow up
with a homerun,

08:58.726 --> 08:59.859
like <i>Gatsby,</i>

08:59.893 --> 09:03.196
or I am out.

09:06.900 --> 09:08.735
Hello, stranger.

09:08.769 --> 09:10.236
Feel like I see you on TV

09:10.270 --> 09:13.139
more than I do in real life.

09:13.173 --> 09:15.074
Might almost believe
you were avoiding my calls.

09:15.109 --> 09:16.342
Of course not.

09:16.377 --> 09:18.011
I'm just really busy right now.

09:18.045 --> 09:20.380
Ticket sales haven't been
as good as Eileen had hoped,

09:20.414 --> 09:23.249
so she's pimping me out
wherever she can.

09:23.283 --> 09:24.684
Okay.

09:24.718 --> 09:25.985
Why don't I come by
after the show?

09:26.019 --> 09:27.754
I can get you off the streets
for a night.

09:27.788 --> 09:28.788
Can't.

09:28.789 --> 09:32.392
I'm moderating a Q&A for
Tom and Julia at table 46.

09:32.426 --> 09:34.727
Oh, fair enough.

09:34.762 --> 09:35.928
How about tomorrow?

09:35.963 --> 09:37.196
Group sales event.

09:37.231 --> 09:39.632
Okay. Friday?

09:39.666 --> 09:41.567
Uh, listen, Derek,
can I call you back?

09:41.602 --> 09:44.604
I have a phone interview
that's about to start.

09:44.638 --> 09:45.638
Bye.

09:49.043 --> 09:50.376
[Groans]

09:50.411 --> 09:53.679
- Where'd you go last night?
- Oh! Ah.

09:53.714 --> 09:54.781
I don't know.

09:54.815 --> 09:56.582
There was a lot
of tequila involved.

09:56.617 --> 09:58.317
I hope it was worth it,
because you just lost us

09:58.352 --> 10:01.721
the cover of <i>New York Magazine.</i>

10:01.755 --> 10:03.756
You better get it together,
or seriously...

10:03.791 --> 10:05.058
What? Or what?

10:05.092 --> 10:06.292
The show's gonna close?

10:06.326 --> 10:08.227
The run is sold out, Kyle.
Come on.

10:08.262 --> 10:10.730
[Door opens]

10:10.764 --> 10:11.998
How's he doing?

10:12.032 --> 10:14.300
He's detoxing.
I hope.

10:14.335 --> 10:15.635
Let me know
if you need any help.

10:15.669 --> 10:18.237
- Thanks.
- I'm right here.

10:18.272 --> 10:20.373
[Snickers]

10:20.407 --> 10:21.741
Are you guys still together?

10:21.775 --> 10:23.209
Of course.

10:23.243 --> 10:24.477
I thought for sure
you'd have told him

10:24.511 --> 10:25.778
about your little affair
by now.

10:25.813 --> 10:26.946
Shut up.

10:26.980 --> 10:28.614
I should've never told you
about Tom.

10:28.649 --> 10:29.730
Hey, hey, there's no shame.

10:29.750 --> 10:30.950
[Laughs]

10:30.984 --> 10:32.518
I was drunk and star-struck.

10:32.553 --> 10:33.853
Oh, what, the first time.

10:33.887 --> 10:35.688
What about the other two
you told me about, huh?

10:35.723 --> 10:37.724
Well, he's pretty great...

10:37.758 --> 10:39.325
Oh, hey, is this where
the auditions

10:39.360 --> 10:40.927
for Jesse are happening?

10:44.865 --> 10:48.468
[Humming]

10:48.502 --> 10:50.770
♪ There's a block
on the edge of this town ♪

10:50.804 --> 10:54.607
♪ no one talks about

10:54.641 --> 10:56.075
♪ where the train
doesn't stop ♪

10:56.110 --> 11:00.279
♪ and the kids know
they're not getting out ♪

11:00.314 --> 11:03.516
♪ you live in a loop
of smokes on the stoop ♪

11:03.550 --> 11:06.686
♪ counting the coins you got ♪

11:06.720 --> 11:09.956
♪ you work at a bar
where all that you are ♪

11:09.990 --> 11:12.158
♪ is everything

11:12.192 --> 11:15.228
♪ you're not

11:15.262 --> 11:16.396
What the hell, Derek?

11:16.430 --> 11:18.665
Excuse me.
This is a private audition.

11:18.699 --> 11:19.699
For my part?

11:19.700 --> 11:22.502
No, for your understudy,
genius.

11:22.536 --> 11:23.736
Been seeing people all week.

11:23.771 --> 11:26.305
You'd know that
if you were ever here.

11:26.340 --> 11:28.307
This is Sam Strickland.

11:28.342 --> 11:30.109
He was in the ensemble
of <i>Bombshell.</i>

11:30.144 --> 11:32.145
Well, then, he should probably
audition for the ensemble

11:32.179 --> 11:34.414
of <i>Hit List</i> and not my part.

11:34.448 --> 11:36.315
Well, guess what?
That's not your call.

11:36.350 --> 11:37.583
Sam's a great talent.

11:37.618 --> 11:39.085
He just hasn't found
the right role yet.

11:39.119 --> 11:42.622
Oh, I know that you're
a visionary, Derek,

11:42.656 --> 11:44.357
but I think you're losing
your touch.

11:44.391 --> 11:45.525
Get him out of here,
please, Kyle.

11:45.559 --> 11:46.693
Oh, no, don't worry.
I'm leaving.

11:46.727 --> 11:49.195
I... my buzz just wore off.

11:49.229 --> 11:51.597
- Bye-bye.
- Jimmy...

11:53.033 --> 11:54.867
So now you see why we're
looking for his understudy.

11:54.902 --> 11:56.736
Yeah, so what do you
want to do?

11:56.770 --> 11:58.438
You want me
to start again, or...

11:58.472 --> 12:00.106
Just take a minute.

12:00.140 --> 12:01.174
We'll go from the top.

12:01.208 --> 12:02.208
I'm sorry about that.

12:02.242 --> 12:04.310
No, don't worry about it.

12:04.344 --> 12:05.545
Don't worry about it.
Okay.

12:05.579 --> 12:06.579
I'll be right back.

12:06.580 --> 12:08.314
What a jackass.

12:08.348 --> 12:10.817
Adam was right.

12:10.851 --> 12:12.151
[Sighs]

12:12.186 --> 12:13.619
I just don't want the show
to get screwed up

12:13.654 --> 12:15.054
just because I broke up
with him.

12:15.089 --> 12:16.356
It won't.

12:16.390 --> 12:18.491
And look, even if it does,
that's not on you.

12:18.525 --> 12:21.160
Yes, it is.

12:21.195 --> 12:23.730
She begged him to open up
to her for months,

12:23.764 --> 12:25.031
and when he finally did,

12:25.065 --> 12:26.705
she didn't like
what she heard and bailed.

12:26.734 --> 12:29.335
And then she brought her friend
in to audition for his part.

12:29.370 --> 12:31.437
That's not exactly
how that happened.

12:31.472 --> 12:33.106
Yeah, actually, it is.

12:33.140 --> 12:34.774
And since I seem to be
the only one

12:34.808 --> 12:35.942
who really cares about him,

12:35.976 --> 12:37.477
I'm gonna go make sure
he's okay.

12:37.511 --> 12:40.346
Whatever.

12:40.381 --> 12:43.950
Yes, we'd be absolutely
delighted to do a performance

12:43.984 --> 12:47.020
at the Brighton Beach Senior Center.

12:47.054 --> 12:50.156
On Monday at 11:00
good for you?

12:50.190 --> 12:51.290
Excellent.

12:51.325 --> 12:53.493
Terrific. Thanks.
Bye.

12:55.996 --> 12:57.063
What's going on?

12:57.097 --> 12:58.965
Did you know
half my producer clients

12:58.999 --> 13:00.867
are going to see
<i>Hit List</i> tonight?

13:00.901 --> 13:02.602
Well, good for them.

13:02.636 --> 13:04.904
It seems M.T.W.
is trying

13:04.938 --> 13:07.640
to move the show to Broadway
this season.

13:07.674 --> 13:09.776
Well, from what I saw
at the winter benefit,

13:09.810 --> 13:12.578
I wouldn't have said
that the show was big enough

13:12.613 --> 13:13.946
for a Broadway transfer.

13:13.981 --> 13:15.782
Well, apparently,
they've made some changes.

13:15.816 --> 13:17.750
Just like that,
you have competition.

13:17.785 --> 13:20.119
And what would you like me
to do with that information?

13:20.154 --> 13:23.089
I'd like you
to get us two tickets

13:23.123 --> 13:24.590
so we can see what kind
of threat

13:24.625 --> 13:26.626
we have on our hands.

13:26.660 --> 13:28.261
I'm sorry, but that's a pass.

13:28.295 --> 13:32.165
Eileen, everybody's looking
for their next project.

13:32.199 --> 13:35.201
Maybe you should too.

13:40.507 --> 13:42.342
What did you think, Jimmy?

13:42.376 --> 13:44.744
You'd just go A.W.O.L. for a
week, and nothing would happen?

13:44.778 --> 13:46.079
Well, I was a little late
a couple times.

13:46.113 --> 13:47.180
I'm sorry.

13:47.214 --> 13:49.482
I don't see why everyone's
making such a big deal about it.

13:49.516 --> 13:50.583
People are coming tonight

13:50.617 --> 13:53.152
who could bring this show
to Broadway.

13:53.187 --> 13:54.187
Our show.

13:54.188 --> 13:55.588
It's what we always wanted.

13:55.622 --> 13:57.990
Doesn't that mean anything
to you anymore?

13:58.025 --> 14:00.293
Don't blow everything up

14:00.327 --> 14:03.363
just because somebody
broke your heart.

14:06.900 --> 14:11.037
This sounds stupid, but it's...

14:11.071 --> 14:12.572
[Sighs]

14:12.606 --> 14:14.807
I don't know, I...

14:14.842 --> 14:16.375
I thought maybe
she was the one.

14:16.410 --> 14:19.345
[Scoffs]

14:19.379 --> 14:21.314
I'm not really sure
there is a one.

14:21.348 --> 14:25.718
Says the guy who just cheated
on his boyfriend.

14:25.753 --> 14:27.120
I hate you.

14:27.154 --> 14:29.622
No, you don't.
I keep you honest.

14:29.656 --> 14:31.924
Look, my parents
are coming tonight.

14:31.959 --> 14:33.359
We're taking Blake to dinner
before the show.

14:33.394 --> 14:35.495
They would love to see you.

14:35.529 --> 14:36.529
You want to come?

14:36.530 --> 14:38.564
Sure, what time?

14:38.599 --> 14:41.901
[Door opens and slams]
All right, children.

14:41.935 --> 14:43.803
Okay, good news and bad news.

14:43.837 --> 14:45.805
The good news is
I found your understudy.

14:45.839 --> 14:47.473
So next time you go
on a bender,

14:47.508 --> 14:49.075
the show won't suffer.

14:49.109 --> 14:50.877
- No, only the audience.
- [Laughs]

14:50.911 --> 14:53.613
Yeah, and the bad news...

14:53.647 --> 14:56.249
I have finally lost
my sense of humor.

14:56.283 --> 14:58.217
This is the biggest night
in <i>Hit List's</i> life.

14:58.252 --> 14:59.819
All right?

14:59.853 --> 15:01.254
It's bigger
than critic previews.

15:01.288 --> 15:03.690
It's bigger than opening night.

15:03.724 --> 15:05.124
And if you don't pull it off,
sunshine,

15:05.159 --> 15:07.193
Sam Strickland is not gonna be
your understudy tomorrow.

15:07.227 --> 15:09.629
He's gonna be your replacement.

15:16.083 --> 15:20.184
Oh, my God, look at that!
"Book by Kyle Bishop."

15:20.236 --> 15:21.936
- Mom, shh.
- Hey... sorry.

15:21.971 --> 15:23.104
I just wanted to say
I'm a big fan.

15:23.139 --> 15:25.674
I've seen the show
like three times.

15:25.708 --> 15:27.309
- Oh, thank you so much.
- You want his autograph?

15:27.343 --> 15:28.777
- Mom.
- You want mine, then?

15:28.811 --> 15:30.178
- I'm his mother.
- Oh, my God.

15:30.212 --> 15:31.746
Will you please make it stop?

15:31.781 --> 15:33.248
What? You should be
enjoying this.

15:33.282 --> 15:35.162
Look at all these people
lined up for your show.

15:35.184 --> 15:36.184
That's what I keep telling him.

15:36.218 --> 15:37.619
We are so proud of you.

15:37.653 --> 15:39.054
It's such a big achievement.

15:39.088 --> 15:40.488
Well, it's not just mine.

15:40.523 --> 15:42.057
You should be proud
of Jimmy too.

15:42.091 --> 15:43.958
Well, of course we're
proud of him.

15:43.993 --> 15:46.094
I wish he would have come out
with us so I could've told him.

15:46.128 --> 15:47.929
Wanna see if he's shown up yet?

15:47.963 --> 15:49.831
- Is he using again?
- Marie!

15:49.865 --> 15:52.934
- Mom, please.
- It's a fair question.

15:52.968 --> 15:54.569
Look, you know we love him,

15:54.603 --> 15:56.905
but this is your moment, honey.

15:56.939 --> 15:59.774
I just want you to make sure
you really take it.

15:59.809 --> 16:01.209
I am.

16:02.244 --> 16:05.714
So?
How did Scott take it?

16:05.748 --> 16:07.749
He didn't have to.

16:07.783 --> 16:10.518
I'm doing <i>Gatsby</i>
with him in the fall.

16:10.553 --> 16:13.955
I made a promise.
I'm not gonna break it.

16:16.158 --> 16:17.559
What about your promise to me,

16:17.593 --> 16:18.693
your commitment to me?

16:18.728 --> 16:20.495
I am totally committed to you.

16:20.529 --> 16:22.664
I will make you the priority.

16:22.698 --> 16:25.333
Anything that you want
to do with me comes first.

16:25.368 --> 16:27.736
I'll work on <i>Gatsby</i>
in my spare time.

16:27.770 --> 16:29.170
We're supposed to work
on everything together.

16:29.205 --> 16:33.308
That's what a partnership is.

16:33.342 --> 16:35.009
So if you had gotten
<i>City of Angels,</i>

16:35.044 --> 16:37.479
I would've directed it too?

16:37.513 --> 16:39.714
We didn't direct
<i>Bombshell</i> together.

16:39.749 --> 16:41.483
And that was a problem,
apparently.

16:41.517 --> 16:45.387
How was it a problem?
I was totally behind you.

16:45.421 --> 16:46.688
Why wouldn't you do
the same for me?

16:46.722 --> 16:48.690
It's one play.

16:48.724 --> 16:51.026
One play you optioned
in our company name.

16:51.060 --> 16:54.729
Legally, that makes it
half mine.

16:54.764 --> 16:55.997
Hey, guys.

16:56.032 --> 16:59.034
Packed house in here.
You ready?

17:02.571 --> 17:03.905
Hey, Daryl.
Good to see you.

17:03.939 --> 17:05.607
Hi.

17:05.641 --> 17:07.242
- Hey, Daryl.
- Hi, Kev.

17:07.276 --> 17:08.242
I didn't know
you would be here.

17:08.277 --> 17:09.678
- Well, yes. How are you?
- Good.

17:09.712 --> 17:12.247
Yeah, I thought you two could arm
wrestle a bit during intermission.

17:12.281 --> 17:14.549
Winner takes the show
to Broadway.

17:14.583 --> 17:17.252
Kevin's been working it.

17:17.286 --> 17:20.288
[Doing vocal exercises]

17:22.724 --> 17:26.161
It's 10 till.
What do you want me to do?

17:26.194 --> 17:27.796
We'll have to cancel.

17:27.829 --> 17:30.832
No, please,
give him five more minutes.

17:30.866 --> 17:32.967
- You're late.
- [Sighs]

17:33.002 --> 17:35.770
If we were on Broadway,
you'd get a fine.

17:35.805 --> 17:37.105
But we're not, are we?

17:37.139 --> 17:38.807
Not yet.

17:38.841 --> 17:41.409
You gonna get out of my way
so I can go get dressed?

17:41.444 --> 17:44.446
Oh, I'd love to.

18:02.865 --> 18:05.133
Jimmy, it's places.

18:05.167 --> 18:08.169
Yeah, ready.

18:13.876 --> 18:15.977
I thought you said
there was no way in hell

18:16.012 --> 18:19.180
Eileen Rand would ever produce
this show on Broadway.

18:19.215 --> 18:20.281
There isn't.

18:20.316 --> 18:22.584
What's she doing here?

18:22.618 --> 18:23.852
Ladies and gentlemen,

18:23.886 --> 18:25.120
we'd like to take
this opportunity

18:25.154 --> 18:27.522
to remind you
that the use of cell phones

18:27.556 --> 18:30.892
and other recording devices
is not only permitted,

18:30.926 --> 18:32.327
but encouraged.

18:32.361 --> 18:35.196
Record the show in its entirety
for all we care.

18:35.231 --> 18:37.298
We don't own it
any more than you do.

18:37.333 --> 18:41.002
[Scattered chuckles]

18:43.339 --> 18:46.741
♪ And now I'm falling

18:46.776 --> 18:49.210
♪ baby, through the sky

18:49.245 --> 18:51.379
♪ through the sky

18:51.414 --> 18:54.516
♪ I'm falling, baby

18:54.550 --> 18:57.819
♪ through the sky

19:00.856 --> 19:03.256
♪

19:08.497 --> 19:11.499
Where is he?

19:17.340 --> 19:19.808
♪ There's a block
on the edge of this town ♪

19:19.842 --> 19:23.545
♪ no one talks about

19:23.579 --> 19:25.213
♪ where the train
doesn't stop ♪

19:25.247 --> 19:29.184
♪ and the kids know
they're not getting out ♪

19:29.218 --> 19:32.487
♪ you live in a loop
of smokes on the stoop ♪

19:32.521 --> 19:35.323
♪ counting the coins you got ♪

19:35.358 --> 19:38.560
♪ you work at a bar
where all that you are ♪

19:38.594 --> 19:44.666
♪ is everything you're not

19:44.700 --> 19:47.268
Rodgers and Hammerstein.

19:47.303 --> 19:48.536
Lerner and Loewe.

19:48.571 --> 19:50.105
Kander and Ebb.

19:50.139 --> 19:52.073
Houston and Levitt.

19:52.108 --> 19:53.641
You two have
one of the longest,

19:53.676 --> 19:56.945
most celebrated writing
partnerships on Broadway.

19:56.979 --> 19:59.047
It must be like a marriage.

19:59.081 --> 20:00.415
- It is.
- Yeah.

20:00.449 --> 20:02.417
With peaks and valleys.

20:02.451 --> 20:04.552
Deep, deep valleys.

20:04.587 --> 20:06.454
[Laughter]

20:06.489 --> 20:09.591
Tell us, what does it take
to keep your marriage alive?

20:09.625 --> 20:11.426
Work.

20:11.460 --> 20:13.695
Hard work.

20:13.729 --> 20:15.430
And communication.

20:15.464 --> 20:17.899
And the ability to put
someone else's needs

20:17.933 --> 20:19.734
before your own.

20:19.769 --> 20:23.171
And the ability to put
the partnership

20:23.205 --> 20:25.507
above everything else.

20:25.541 --> 20:28.543
Okay.
Let's talk about process.

20:28.577 --> 20:32.714
Say you're writing a song,
and you disagree on a lyric.

20:32.748 --> 20:34.649
How do you decide
who gets their way?

20:34.684 --> 20:36.951
We never really disagree
on lyrics.

20:36.986 --> 20:38.953
No.
Because she writes them.

20:38.988 --> 20:41.089
[Laughter]

20:41.123 --> 20:45.060
Well, what about a story point
or characters?

20:45.094 --> 20:48.096
I personally know
that Marilyn's mother, Gladys,

20:48.130 --> 20:49.597
came in and out of the story
several times

20:49.632 --> 20:51.166
before you made a decision.

20:51.200 --> 20:52.600
Well, then we talk about it

20:52.635 --> 20:54.769
until we're both comfortable
with the answer.

20:54.804 --> 20:57.072
Or Julia gets her way.

20:57.106 --> 21:00.342
Or Tom acts passive-aggressive
until he gets his way.

21:00.376 --> 21:02.277
Or Julia makes a decision
without telling me,

21:02.311 --> 21:03.845
and I find out about it later.

21:03.879 --> 21:06.114
Or Tom calls his lawyer.

21:06.148 --> 21:07.182
[Crowd murmurs]

21:07.216 --> 21:08.750
[Laughs awkwardly] Okay.

21:08.784 --> 21:10.785
Uh, let's open it up
for some questions.

21:10.820 --> 21:12.821
Um, yes, you, sir.

21:12.855 --> 21:15.490
What are you doing next?

21:15.524 --> 21:18.426
We're doing <i>The Great Gatsby.</i>

21:18.461 --> 21:21.262
No. No, we're not.

21:21.297 --> 21:25.200
What he meant to say is
I am, as a play,

21:25.234 --> 21:26.835
at Manhattan theatre workshop,

21:26.869 --> 21:29.003
with Scott Nichols directing.

21:29.038 --> 21:31.006
So you're not working
together anymore.

21:31.040 --> 21:34.943
- Well, of course we are.
- No.

21:34.977 --> 21:37.479
We're not.

21:47.162 --> 21:50.931
♪ I wish I never knew you

21:50.965 --> 21:54.202
♪ love

21:55.136 --> 22:01.542
♪ I wish you were a bad girl ♪

22:01.576 --> 22:05.212
♪ I wish I never knew you

22:05.246 --> 22:08.148
♪ love

22:08.183 --> 22:12.152
♪ why is this pain so

22:12.187 --> 22:16.390
♪ unforgettable

22:16.424 --> 22:18.726
Sorry I couldn't make it
back here all day.

22:18.760 --> 22:19.800
Have you written anything?

22:19.828 --> 22:21.795
I started working on something,

22:21.830 --> 22:23.964
but it's still in process,
you know.

22:23.998 --> 22:25.999
Okay.

22:26.034 --> 22:27.801
Let's hear what you got.

22:27.836 --> 22:33.073
♪ I wish you were a bad man ♪

22:33.108 --> 22:34.608
You wanna try?

22:34.642 --> 22:35.843
Yeah, okay.

22:35.877 --> 22:38.045
Ready?

22:38.079 --> 22:44.451
♪ I wish you were a bad man ♪

22:44.486 --> 22:50.824
♪ I wish you made it easier

22:50.859 --> 22:54.928
♪ I wish you'd done something ♪

22:54.963 --> 22:59.600
♪ unforgivable

22:59.634 --> 23:04.204
♪

23:04.239 --> 23:06.840
♪ 'cause holding on to you

23:06.875 --> 23:10.711
♪ is all that I can do
until I learn ♪

23:10.745 --> 23:17.184
♪ the hands around the throat
are my own ♪

23:17.218 --> 23:19.820
♪ don't let me know

23:19.854 --> 23:21.555
♪ if it hurts

23:21.589 --> 23:23.457
♪ if it hurts you

23:23.491 --> 23:26.059
♪ I don't want to be

23:26.094 --> 23:29.730
♪ your friend
that you turn to ♪

23:29.764 --> 23:32.800
♪ that you
won't pull me close ♪

23:32.834 --> 23:38.071
♪ but you can't let me go ♪

23:38.106 --> 23:41.508
♪ don't let me know

23:41.543 --> 23:44.645
♪ don't let me know

23:44.679 --> 23:47.681
♪ don't let me know

23:47.716 --> 23:51.485
♪ don't let me know

23:51.519 --> 23:57.691
both:
♪ I wish I'd never met you

23:57.725 --> 24:03.931
♪ now I gotta forget again

24:03.965 --> 24:08.268
♪ I wish you didn't know me

24:08.303 --> 24:13.240
♪ so damn well

24:13.274 --> 24:17.311
♪ mm-mm

24:17.345 --> 24:20.347
♪ don't tell me
that you're scared ♪

24:20.382 --> 24:22.116
♪ every time

24:22.150 --> 24:24.418
He's not supposed to walk away.

24:24.452 --> 24:27.254
It's not anything I think
the audience will notice.

24:27.288 --> 24:30.157
I notice.

24:30.191 --> 24:32.793
♪ Oh, don't let me know

24:32.827 --> 24:34.561
♪ if it hurts

24:34.596 --> 24:37.531
♪ if it hurts you

24:37.565 --> 24:39.967
♪ I don't want to be

24:40.001 --> 24:43.370
♪ your friend
that you turn to ♪

24:43.405 --> 24:46.440
♪ that you won't
pull me close ♪

24:46.474 --> 24:51.812
♪ but you can't let go

24:51.846 --> 24:55.115
♪ don't let me know

24:55.150 --> 24:57.618
♪ don't let me know

24:57.652 --> 25:01.221
♪ don't let me know

25:01.256 --> 25:05.092
♪ don't let me know

25:05.126 --> 25:08.562
♪ if you think
there's a chance ♪

25:08.596 --> 25:11.765
♪ you could fall again

25:11.800 --> 25:13.400
What's going on?

25:13.435 --> 25:16.270
Now what's he doing
in the middle of the dancers?

25:16.304 --> 25:22.476
♪ Stop loving me

25:22.510 --> 25:24.745
♪ don't let me know

25:24.779 --> 25:28.782
♪ if it hurts,
if it hurts you ♪

25:28.817 --> 25:30.951
♪ I don't want to be

25:30.985 --> 25:34.621
♪ your friend
that you turn to ♪

25:34.656 --> 25:37.791
♪ that you won't
pull me close ♪

25:37.826 --> 25:42.896
♪ but you can't let go

25:42.931 --> 25:46.033
♪ don't let me know

25:46.067 --> 25:48.869
♪ don't let me know

25:48.903 --> 25:53.640
♪ don't let me know

25:53.675 --> 25:56.910
♪ don't let me

25:56.945 --> 26:01.315
♪ know

26:01.349 --> 26:03.617
Did you mean
what you said in there?

26:03.651 --> 26:05.352
That the partnership's over?

26:05.386 --> 26:06.620
If you were being honest,

26:06.654 --> 26:08.021
you know that's what
you think too.

26:08.056 --> 26:09.857
That couldn't be further
from the truth.

26:09.891 --> 26:11.725
Come on.

26:11.760 --> 26:13.060
Clearly you've been
unhappy with me.

26:13.094 --> 26:15.062
You've been auditioning
new partners all year.

26:15.096 --> 26:17.466
First it was Peter.
Now it's Scott.

26:17.633 --> 26:18.733
Jimmy, Kyle.

26:18.800 --> 26:20.868
You told me last week

26:20.902 --> 26:23.871
that all you want to do
is direct.

26:23.905 --> 26:26.974
Look, maybe we're just going
in different directions.

26:27.008 --> 26:28.909
Or maybe this partnership
only works

26:28.943 --> 26:30.210
when it's all about you.

26:30.245 --> 26:33.347
I spent the last six months
taking care of you

26:33.381 --> 26:35.315
after you dropped the ball
in Boston

26:35.350 --> 26:36.850
and your marriage fell apart.

26:36.885 --> 26:39.853
But the moment I get
something I want,

26:39.888 --> 26:41.368
you can't even wait
six months for me.

26:41.389 --> 26:44.091
You didn't ask me to wait.

26:44.125 --> 26:46.360
I didn't ask you
to take care of me, either.

26:46.394 --> 26:50.998
But I am asking that you be
okay with me doing this.

26:51.032 --> 26:52.533
Tom, I love it.

26:52.567 --> 26:55.402
It is the first thing
that has really made me happy

26:55.436 --> 26:58.572
in years.

26:58.606 --> 27:01.175
Thank you so much.

27:01.209 --> 27:03.811
We have our answer.

27:03.845 --> 27:07.080
That's not what I meant.

27:07.115 --> 27:09.750
