and I did.

33:44.105 --> 33:45.339
I was on fire.

33:45.373 --> 33:46.540
No, you were high.

33:46.574 --> 33:48.208
And you hurt Karen
and freaked everybody out,

33:48.243 --> 33:51.044
and now Derek and Scott
are gonna fire you.

33:51.079 --> 33:52.779
No. No. Can't do that.

33:52.814 --> 33:54.081
Yes, they can.
They already did.

33:54.115 --> 33:56.249
Sam's going on as soon as
he can get off book.

33:56.284 --> 33:59.886
[Exhales]
And what did you say, Kyle?

33:59.921 --> 34:01.955
I told them that it was
the right thing to do.

34:01.990 --> 34:03.957
You took their side.

34:03.992 --> 34:07.227
Jimmy, I have been
on your side my entire life.

34:07.262 --> 34:09.463
I've stood up for you
when nobody else would.

34:09.496 --> 34:11.465
I was the one who got you
out of the situation with Adam.

34:11.498 --> 34:12.966
If it wasn't for me,
you'd probably be dead

34:13.001 --> 34:14.333
in a gutter somewhere.

34:14.369 --> 34:15.802
I have to stop helping you.

34:15.837 --> 34:19.840
You have to start
helping yourself.

34:19.873 --> 34:21.842
Right.

34:21.876 --> 34:23.777
Hey, all right, listen up!

34:23.811 --> 34:25.344
Everybody!

34:25.380 --> 34:27.380
Whoa, hey!
Oh, wow.

34:27.415 --> 34:29.616
Uh, okay, look.

34:29.650 --> 34:30.951
I just want to say

34:30.985 --> 34:33.219
that it turns out

34:33.254 --> 34:35.155
tonight was my final
performance of <i>Hit List.</i>

34:35.188 --> 34:36.657
[Crowd booing]

34:36.690 --> 34:37.925
I mean, yeah, yeah.
Apparently...

34:37.958 --> 34:39.493
Apparently, the "creative team"
has decided

34:39.527 --> 34:41.929
that... that they no longer
require my services,

34:41.963 --> 34:43.030
and when I say "creative team,"

34:43.063 --> 34:45.232
I mean that term, like,
very loosely,

34:45.266 --> 34:47.501
seeing as I'm the only one
that did anything

34:47.534 --> 34:48.635
anyway, right?

34:48.670 --> 34:49.770
[Laughing]

34:49.804 --> 34:51.972
Uh, I would like
to thank Karen,

34:52.005 --> 34:54.274
Karen Cartwright,

34:54.309 --> 34:56.176
for bringing this show to life

34:56.210 --> 34:58.178
by stringing along its director

34:58.212 --> 35:00.514
and for believing me
as an actor so much

35:00.548 --> 35:02.316
that she engineered
my replacement,

35:02.350 --> 35:04.885
which made perfect sense,
considering that real emotion,

35:04.919 --> 35:07.621
on stage or off,
is way too scary for her.

35:07.655 --> 35:10.958
I would also like to thank,
uh, Kyle,

35:10.992 --> 35:14.428
Kyle Bishop, my lifelong friend
and writing partner,

35:14.462 --> 35:16.196
for his unwavering loyalty

35:16.230 --> 35:17.631
throughout this entire process.

35:17.665 --> 35:19.366
Oh, wait, did I say loyalty?

35:19.400 --> 35:22.302
I mean for screwing me
the second he had the chance.

35:22.337 --> 35:23.637
For the record, Blake,

35:23.671 --> 35:26.039
Kyle was also screwing
Tom Levitt last week.

35:26.074 --> 35:27.674
